visual.name: htmlContent
visual.description: Visualise column or measure values as HTML in your Power BI reports.

en-US.Landing_Page_Overview_1: Thanks very much for using this visual!
en-US.Landing_Page_Overview_2: To get started you simply need to add a measure or field that contains your HTML to the Values field in the properties pane, and the visual will attempt to render it for you.
en-US.Landing_Page_Overview_3: Please note that there are some limitations to this, due to the security limitations imposed upon Power BI custom visuals.
en-US.Landing_Page_Overview_4: You can visit the visual's home page by clicking the question mark icon in the top-right of this page.
en-US.Roles_Values_Description: Field values or measures containing the desired HTML data to render.
en-US.Roles_Sampling_Description: Because some results can aggregate to a single value, you can add a grouping value to this field to ensure that all discrete values are displayed in the visual.
en-US.Objects_ContentFormatting_Separation_Des: Options to separate multiple values in the rendered output.
en-US.Objects_ContentFormatting_ShowRawHTML_De: Display the data as raw HTML, rather than rendered HTML.
